  <prompt>
    <goal>Trim infrastructure/integration architecture docs to decisions-only</goal>
    <context>The infrastructure and integration architecture documents contain deployment procedures, configuration walkthroughs, and implementation details that belong in scripts or .claude/skills/. This task trims each file to retain only infrastructure decisions, integration boundaries, and architectural constraints.</context>
    <constraints>Preserve all decision/constraint content, especially security boundaries, environment configuration decisions, and packaging strategies. Do not remove ADR references or deployment topology decisions. Only touch infrastructure/integration docs listed in this task.</constraints>
  </prompt>
  <knowledge>
    <files>
      <file>projects/ai-procedure-refactoring-r1/spec.md</file>
      <file>projects/ai-procedure-refactoring-r1/design.md</file>
    </files>
  </knowledge>
  <steps>
    1. Read notes/architecture-audit.md for classification guidance on infrastructure docs.
    2. Read each target file fully:
       - docs/architecture/external-access-spa-architecture.md (trim)
       - docs/architecture/communication-service-architecture.md (trim)
       - docs/architecture/email-to-document-*.md (trim — glob for all matching files)
       - docs/architecture/office-outlook-teams-*.md (trim — glob for all matching files)
       - docs/architecture/BFF-RENAME-AND-CONFIG-STRATEGY.md (trim)
       - docs/architecture/INFRASTRUCTURE-PACKAGING-STRATEGY.md (trim)
       - docs/architecture/multi-environment-portability-strategy.md (trim)
    3. For each file, identify and remove:
       - Step-by-step deployment procedures
       - Configuration file contents and setup walkthroughs
       - CLI command sequences that belong in scripts
       - Implementation timelines and migration checklists
    4. Preserve:
       - Infrastructure topology decisions
       - Security boundaries and authentication flows
       - Environment strategy and packaging decisions
       - ADR references and architectural constraints
    5. Record before/after line counts for each file.
  </steps>
  <tools>Read, Edit, Glob, Grep, Bash</tools>
  <outputs>
    - Trimmed: All infrastructure/integration architecture docs listed above
    - Before/after line counts recorded
